cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with hyperspectral imaging and unmixing, which are common topics in computer vision. The use of learning-based sparsity also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of image grids and the evaluation of results suggest a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
